sect1.para:
There are several healthcare delivery systems in the United States that aim to provide preventative care to help individuals maintain health, provide resources, educate them on treatment options, and deliver treatments when an injury, disease, or illness develops (IOM,
         2003
      ). Healthcare systems typically involve the facilities where care is delivered (i. e., hospitals, residential and home care services), long-term care, clinics, and offices, as well as the individuals providing care (i. e., physicians, nurses, dieticians, pharmacists, physical and occupational therapists, social workers, and psychologists).
